Northeastern University Living Learning Communities (LLCs)

Overview
Large part of college experience takes place in residence halls. To make most of first year at Northeastern, students participate in Living Learning Community (LLC). LLCs bring students with similar interests, hobbies, and courses together for support and fun throughout their journey as young Husky. There's a community for everyone.

First Year Residential Experience

Goals
New students living in university housing participate in First Year Residential Experience at Northeastern University. Two main goals:
1. Create opportunities for social connection, support, and belonging
2. Provide first-year students with opportunities for learning and development

Core Outcome
Prepare students to become lifelong learners who are holistically formed, experience growth alongside others, and are responsible contributors to local and global communities. Residential Life team designs intentional experiences, programs, and activities to build strong community environment prioritizing both goals.

Living Learning Communities Structure
Central component of First Year Residential Experience is LLCs. When incoming first-year students apply for housing, they choose from more than dozen LLCs to begin residential experience at Northeastern. LLCs bring together students with shared personal or academic interest to learn and grow during first year.

Each LLC directed by Residential Life staff, as well as staff and faculty from across university. Team provides support, facilitates intentional learning opportunities, and strives to foster meaningful connections within community.

First Year College Affiliated LLCs

Bouvé College of Health Sciences LLC
Focus: Leadership in health care field
Unites students from many majors including Physical Therapy, Nursing, Health Science, and Pharmacy for interdisciplinary learning experience. In modern health care field, practitioners work closely in team setting across multiple disciplines.

LLC allows students to gain intimate understanding of this complex but exciting environment. Students spend time with faculty members during dinner series and gain academic support for challenging course loads.

Partner: Bouvé College of Health Sciences

Khoury College of Computer Sciences LLC
Focus: Programming, computer sciences, and technology
Founded on hard drives, programming, and C++ Scripts. Beyond basics of Computer Sciences, community offers students academically supportive environment while providing opportunity for socializing, connecting, and building strong network for successful first year.

Students integrate love for Computer Sciences into real-world applications while working with faculty and staff on cutting edge of game design and computer science.

Women in Khoury College of Computer Sciences
Supportive and academically challenging home for women interested in Computer Sciences. Students receive all academic and social support from main LLC plus specialized support through networks and mentorships while at Northeastern and beyond.

Partner: Khoury College of Computer Sciences

College of Engineering LLC
Focus: Engineering, math, and science applications
Oldest Living Learning Community in university housing. Well-established community experiencing Northeastern University and city of Boston through lens of engineer. Students apply love and knowledge of math, science, and engineering to real-world problems while connecting with faculty and staff regularly.

Community provides strong support system for academic course load through weekly tutoring and review sessions.

Partners: College of Engineering, Center for Student Academic Services

College of Science LLC
Focus: Scientific exploration and discovery
Theme: Explore. Discover. Revolutionize.

Students challenged to expand academic horizons. Experience and become part of cutting-edge world of sciences. Encouraged to explore passions through biology, chemistry, physics, psychology, or other science disciplines. Academic support, faculty interactions, co-op and research panels, and applying knowledge in inspired ways all part of College of Science experience.

Residing on interdisciplinary floor affords unique opportunity to learn from peers in other fields and become more informed member of scientific community. Dynamic and stimulating group of students invested in advancing scientific world.

Partners: College of Science, Center for Student Academic Services

D'Amore-McKim School of Business LLCs
Focus: Business careers and professional development
Three business-focused tracks with access to faculty, student co-op panels, and extensive programming for business-minded students:

Corporate Explorers
For students who know business is in their future but unsure of exact path. Opportunity to learn about career options in business field prior to committing to concentration. Programming focuses on self-discovery, professional development, and connecting students to co-ops and faculty members. Events include concentration panels, faculty dinners, and collaboration with Career Development office. Find your niche in business world.

International Business
Focus: Business savvy and cultural competence
Learn about international business trends, effect of global markets, and etiquette needed to conduct business abroad. Programming promotes cultural exchange, fosters collaboration, and emphasizes importance of global connections in business world. Students work closely with faculty in D'Amore-McKim School of Business and have close connection with Office of Global Services (OGS). Strengthens students' academic experience and develops global citizenship.

Women in Business
For students looking to connect with enterprising women sharing interest in business. Community for both women and allies. Opportunity to help plan and organize variety of events and activities for women: managing office politics, networking events with top-level executives, student-led co-op panel, and self-defense demonstration. Programming promotes equity for women in business world, encourages inclusivity, and provides opportunities for leadership and advancement. Members invited to participate in Women in Business Club and Smart Woman Securities organization (focuses on investment education for undergraduates).

Partners: D'Amore-McKim School of Business, International Student & Scholar Institute, Center for Student Academic Services

First Year Interdisciplinary LLCs

Pre-Health LLC
For students aspiring to allopathic (MD), osteopathic, dental, optometry, pediatric, or veterinary medical careers. LLC focuses on educating residents about diverse career options in medicine, showcasing broad array of professional paths.

Academically supportive environment with direct connection to Pre-Health program. Receive guidance to prepare for graduate school and beyond.

Politics, Philosophy, and Economics LLC
Expands classroom learning within cohort of students examining real-world problems while discovering their place in greater global society. In collaboration with College of Social Sciences and Humanities, provides students with variety of engaging and challenging approaches to understanding world around us.

Community Events:
- Metaphysics, Our Existence, and Coffee: Faculty chats on understanding existence
- Quiz Bowl Competition: Team competition on questions specific to politics, philosophy, and economic disciplines
- Boston Politic Tour: Walking tour of important historical places in Boston with lasting impact on government

Honors LLC
From first day on campus, Honors students connected to like-minded peers as they form Living Learning Community focused on theme of mutual interest.

First-year Honors students live together in Honors LLC where they participate in variety of activities to collectively explore interests and connect with one another.

Supported by Honors Living Learning Coordinator (faculty or professional staff member) and upperclass Honors student serving as Honors Living Learning Assistant.

First Year Thematic Based LLCs

Creative Expressions LLC
For students with passion for art in its many mediums. Community affords opportunity to explore many forms of creative expression and how artistic methods can be conveyed.

Whether future career path, deepest passion, or budding hobby, journey of self-discovery and self-expression. Find your niche in Creative Expressions families.

Partners: College of Arts, Media and Design, Department of Art and Design, Department of Theatre, Department of English, Department of Music, College of Arts, Media and Design Advising, College of Social Sciences and Humanities

Cultural Inclusion LLC
Community of open-minded, progressive students interested in exploring who they are, learning from each other, and celebrating diverse perspectives. Gain deeper understanding of both own culture and that of those around you. Collaborate to discover, inform, and applaud differences and similarities of race, culture, gender, and sexual orientation.

Foster greater cultural awareness, embrace diversity of Northeastern population, and strive to create more inclusive environment.

Partners: College of Social Sciences and Humanities, Office of Global Services, Cultural Life at Northeastern, LGBTQA Campus Services

Healthy Living LLC
Focus: Living healthy lifestyle away from home
Members have opportunity to learn how to lead well-balanced life through multiple dimensions of wellness.

Workshops and programs focused on stress management, nutrition, physical activity, spirituality, sustainability, and much more.

Leaders of the Pack LLC
Focus: Developing leadership skills
Discover and develop your style of leadership. Throughout year, experiences and conversations within community allow fine-tuning of leadership skills and connection to powerful network of leaders at Northeastern.

Through academic, service, social, and community-based experiences, opportunity to cultivate the leader in you. Community helps navigate course as leader at Northeastern by networking with faculty members and upperclassmen in leadership positions on campus and within community.

Partners: Student Leadership, Center for Student Involvement

Musical Motifs LLC
For students who play instrument, compose music, sing, or simply enjoy listening. Musical Motifs seeks to connect passion for music with industry skills to create complete, melodious ensemble.

Encouraged to express yourself musically and have opportunity to attend musical events Boston area has to offer.

Partners: Department of English, Department of Music, College of Arts, Media and Design Advising, College of Social Sciences and Humanities

